Scalability and elasticity are core benefits of cloud computing.

Scalability:
The ability to increase or decrease resources based on demand.

Elasticity:
The ability to automatically adjust resources dynamically.

For example, an e-commerce website scales during festival sales and reduces resources afterward.

A real-life use case is streaming platforms handling sudden user spikes.

Another example is gaming servers automatically expanding during peak hours.

Scalability and elasticity improve performance while controlling costs.
